9.Check anagram.

1st approach-->by using dictionary
Store the frequency of every character in a dictionary.
Increase counts for the first string and decrease counts for the second string.

s1="listen"
s2="silent"
if len(s1)!=len(s2):
    print("not anagram")
else:
    freq={}
    for ch in s1:
        if ch in freq:
            freq[ch]+=1
        else:
            freq[ch]=1
    for ch in s2:
        if ch in freq:
            freq[ch]-=1
        else:
            freq[ch]=-1

    is_anagram = True

    for values in freq.values():
        if values!=0:
            is_anagram=False

if is_anagram:
    print("anagram")
else:
    print("not an anagram")

tc=O(n)
